1: To the Chanter, a Psalm of the children of Korah O clap your hands together (all ye people) O sing unto God with the voice of thanksgiving.
2: For the LORD the most highest(hyest) is to be feared, and he is the great King upon all the earth.
3: He shall subdue the people under us, and the Heathen under our feet.
4: He chooseth us for an heritage, the beauty of Jacob whom he loved. Selah.
5: God is gone up with a merry noise, and the LORD with the sound of the trumpet.
6: O Sing praises, sing praises unto God: O sing praises, sing praises unto our King.
7: For God is King of all the earth, O sing praises unto him with understanding.
8: God is king over the Heathen, God sitteth in his holy seat.
9: The princes of the people are gathered together unto the God of Abraham: for God is far higher(farre farre hyer) exalted, than the mighty lords of the earth.
